    {"id":"mara","primary_name":"Mara","alternate_names":["The Tempter","Lord of Death","Pāpīyas"],"tradition_id":"buddhist","earliest_attestation":"Pali Canon (Padhana Sutta)","primary_sources":["Padhana Sutta","Mara Samyutta","Buddhacarita"],"summary":"Cosmic tempter who tried to prevent the Buddha's awakening and keeps beings bound to samsara. Four Maras. Buddhist Tier-3/archonic figure: ruler of the desire-realm who would keep beings within it.","facets":["mara-tempter","mara-lord-of-desire-realm","mara-as-archon"]},
    {"id":"padmasambhava","primary_name":"Padmasambhava","alternate_names":["Guru Rinpoche","Lotus-Born"],"tradition_id":"buddhist","earliest_attestation":"Historical 8th c. CE","primary_sources":["Pema Kathang","terma texts"],"summary":"Tantric master who established Vajrayana in Tibet (8th c.). Born from a lotus. Concealed hidden teachings (terma) for later discovery. 'Second Buddha' to Nyingma school.","facets":["padmasambhava-tantric-master"]},
    # ========== ZOROASTRIAN ==========
    {"id":"ahura-mazda","primary_name":"Ahura Mazda","alternate_names":["Ohrmazd","Hormazd","The Wise Lord"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Gathas c. 1500–1000 BCE","primary_sources":["Gathas","Younger Avesta","Bundahishn"],"etymology":"Avestan ahura ('lord') + mazda ('wise')","iconography":["winged sun-disk (Faravahar)"],"summary":"The Wise Lord. Source of asha (truth, cosmic order). Uncreated, all-good. Creator through his Holy Spirit (Spenta Mainyu). Locked in 12,000-year war with Ahriman, ultimately winning at Frashegird.","facets":["ahura-mazda-wise-lord","ahura-mazda-source-of-asha","ahura-mazda-cosmic-warrior"]},
    {"id":"ahriman","primary_name":"Angra Mainyu","alternate_names":["Ahriman","Hostile Spirit","The Lie"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Gathas","primary_sources":["Gathas","Vendidad","Bundahishn"],"etymology":"Avestan angra ('hostile') + mainyu ('spirit')","summary":"The Hostile Spirit. Source of druj (lie, disorder). Uncreated in classical Zoroastrianism. Creates daevas to counter Amesha Spentas. Ultimate ancestor of Satan as cosmic adversary in Christian theology.","facets":["ahriman-hostile-spirit","ahriman-source-of-lie","ahriman-eschatological-loser"]},
    {"id":"amesha-spentas","primary_name":"The Amesha Spentas","alternate_names":["Bountiful Immortals","Amshaspands"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Gathas","primary_sources":["Gathas","Yashts","Bundahishn"],"summary":"Six (or seven including Spenta Mainyu) divine emanations of Ahura Mazda, each presiding over a good creation: Vohu Manah (Good Mind/cattle), Asha Vahishta (Truth/fire), Khshathra Vairya (Dominion/sky), Spenta Armaiti (Devotion/earth), Haurvatat (Wholeness/waters), Ameretat (Immortality/plants). Probable origin of the seven-fold pattern in late antique angelology.","facets":["amesha-spentas-divine-council"]},
    {"id":"saoshyant","primary_name":"Saoshyant","alternate_names":["Astvat-Ereta","World-Savior"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Younger Avesta","primary_sources":["Yasht 19","Bundahishn"],"summary":"Future savior at the end of cosmic time. Performs the Frashegird, raises the dead, defeats Ahriman. Earliest fully-developed eschatological savior — probable source of Jewish messianism and Christian eschatology via Second Temple Judaism.","facets":["saoshyant-final-savior"]},
    {"id":"yima-first-king","primary_name":"Yima","alternate_names":["Jamshid (Persian)","Yima Khshaeta"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Gathas; major narrative Vendidad 2","primary_sources":["Vendidad 2","Shahnameh"],"etymology":"Avestan Yima — PIE *Yemo 'twin', cognate with Vedic Yama, Old Norse Ymir","summary":"First king of humanity, ruler of golden age. Given the vara (enclosed paradise) by Ahura Mazda to preserve seeds of all life through a coming winter. The Iranian fork of the PIE *Yemo myth.","facets":["yima-golden-age-king","yima-vara-builder","yima-pie-yemo-iranian"]},
    {"id":"zurvan-time","primary_name":"Zurvan","alternate_names":["Zurvan Akarana ('Boundless Time')"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Zurvanite tradition, prominent Sasanian period","primary_sources":["Plutarch","Eznik of Kolb","Manichaean references"],"summary":"In the Zurvanite heresy, Time itself — parent of both Ahura Mazda and Ahriman, born as twins from Zurvan's millennium of doubt. Suppressed by orthodox Zoroastrianism but influential on Manichaeism.","facets":["zurvan-boundless-time","zurvan-parent-of-twins"]},
    {"id":"daevas-zoroastrian","primary_name":"The Daevas","alternate_names":["Devs (Middle Persian)"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Gathas","primary_sources":["Gathas (Yasna 32, 34)","Vendidad","Bundahishn"],"etymology":"Avestan daēva, cognate with Vedic deva — but inverted: daevas are demons in Iranian, gods in Vedic. The linguistic fingerprint of the Indo-Iranian religious schism.","summary":"Hostile spirits aligned with Ahriman. Six chief daevas oppose six Amesha Spentas. Indra is named as a daeva in Vendidad — direct evidence of the schism.","facets":["daevas-zoroastrian-demons","daevas-vedic-deva-inversion"]},
    {"id":"mithra-iranian","primary_name":"Mithra (Iranian)","alternate_names":["Mihr","Mehr"],"tradition_id":"zoroastrian","earliest_attestation":"Younger Avesta; Mitanni treaty 1380 BCE","primary_sources":["Mihr Yasht","Mitanni treaty"],"summary":"Iranian development of contract-deity. 10,000 eyes, 10,000 ears, sees every contract. Mediator between Ahura Mazda and humanity. Source of Roman Mithraic mystery cult.","facets":["mithra-iranian-mediator","mithra-all-seeing-of-contracts"]},
