    {"id":"pangu-primordial-giant","primary_name":"Pangu","alternate_names":["P'an-Ku"],"tradition_id":"taoist","earliest_attestation":"Sanwu Liji (3rd c. CE)","primary_sources":["Sanwu Liji","Wuyun Linian Ji"],"summary":"Primordial giant from whose body the cosmos is constructed. Born inside the cosmic egg. Holds heaven and earth apart for 18,000 years. When he dies: breath = wind/clouds, voice = thunder, left eye = sun, right eye = moon, blood = rivers, hair = stars, fleas = humans. Chinese parallel of Ymir, Puruṣa, PIE *Yemo — with no plausible historical connection. Convergent independent development.","facets":["pangu-cosmic-body","pangu-separator-of-sky-and-earth"]},
